The <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`gitlab.ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`gitlab.ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-go="`ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-python="`ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`gitlab.ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-java="`gitlab.ProjectApprovalRule`" pulumi-lang-hcl="`gitlab_project_approval_rule`">`gitlab.ProjectApprovalRule`</span> resource manages the lifecycle of a project-level approval rule.

> This resource requires a GitLab Enterprise instance.

> A project is limited to one <span pulumi-lang-nodejs=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-dotnet=""AnyApprover"" pulumi-lang-go=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-python=""any_approver"" pulumi-lang-yaml=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-java=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-hcl=""any_approver"">"anyApprover"</span> rule at a time, any attempt to create a second rule of type <span pulumi-lang-nodejs=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-dotnet=""AnyApprover"" pulumi-lang-go=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-python=""any_approver"" pulumi-lang-yaml=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-java=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-hcl=""any_approver"">"anyApprover"</span> will fail. As a result, if 
   an <span pulumi-lang-nodejs=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-dotnet=""AnyApprover"" pulumi-lang-go=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-python=""any_approver"" pulumi-lang-yaml=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-java=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-hcl=""any_approver"">"anyApprover"</span> rule is already present on a project at creation time, and that rule requires 0 approvers, the rule will be automatically imported
   to prevent a common error with this resource.

> Since a project is limited to one <span pulumi-lang-nodejs=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-dotnet=""AnyApprover"" pulumi-lang-go=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-python=""any_approver"" pulumi-lang-yaml=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-java=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-hcl=""any_approver"">"anyApprover"</span> rule, attempting to add two <span pulumi-lang-nodejs=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-dotnet=""AnyApprover"" pulumi-lang-go=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-python=""any_approver"" pulumi-lang-yaml=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-java=""anyApprover"" pulumi-lang-hcl=""any_approver"">"anyApprover"</span> rules to the same project in terraform will result in 
   terraform identifying changes with every "plan" operation, and may result in an error during the "apply" operation.

